                },
                "category": "interaction",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>A ghostly guard suffers from shame when it attacks a target that appears to be an elf or a worshipper of Calistria. Forgive Foe can be attempted against a ghostly guard with a @Check[type:diplomacy|dc:39] check or @Check[type:society|dc:39] check. If a ghostly guard is affected by a critical success from Forgive Foe, it sighs in relief as it fades away, its soul released into the afterlife.</p>"
                },
